But there is still another possibility - the virtual operator.
It was the entry into the market of virtual operators that led to a significant price drop, to which traditional operators would then have to react.
At the same time, even before sharks like Tesko Mobile and Virgin Mobile entered the market, sounds similar to ours resonated in Britain.
However, it has been shown that there is room for such operators and that they can be truly successful.
After all, for examples we do not have to go very far.
In February of this year we have informed you of the arrival of the virtual operator Mobilking in Poland.
In just half a year, this operator has managed to gain more than 100,000 customers and become the fifth largest local operator.
At the same time behind Mobilking is the financial group Penta to which in the Czech Republic belongs among others U:fon.
The advantage of virtual operators is the ability to focus on a much more concrete target group.
In other words, to be able to work effectively, he needs much less customers than a traditional operator.
They do not carry behind, that is, relatively high costs for the creation, operation and maintenance of the mobile network.
Thus, in the world, virtual operators usually present themselves at low cost, offering low-cost calls and SMS, which is often in balance with the narrower service offering.
Thus, for example, Tesco Mobile in the UK offers SMS that cost at least half of its competitors.
But as the example of Mobilking in Poland shows, it can be a pretty good move even to bet on a target group.
This operator focuses, so to speak, specifically on men.
"Real men choose Mobilking operator that they like and can be trusted," says David Seibertz CEO Mobile Entertainment Company who produces this virtual operator.
It is difficult to say if we can also assert a concept similar to that of Poland.
Vodafone press spokesman Miroslav <0xC4><0x8C>epick<0xC3><0xBD> said: “The Czech market is relatively small for a fragmented approach, on which most virtual operators are based.
In addition from the point of view of services is relatively saturated."
In the Czech Republic no possibility, say the operators of the mobile network
But it seems almost certain that if there will ever be an operator in the Czech Republic, Mobilking will not.
“We are talking about the expansion of this successful project, but in the Czech Republic negotiations do not have much expectations.
