The Ministry of the Interior requires that drivers with three administrative penalties for excessive blood alcohol, install in his car the system that prevents driving the vehicle in a state of drunkenness or if he does not blow in the appropriate device.
The measure was announced last June and is already included in the annual report of the Prosecutor General’s Office, according to which it will be a pilot project lasting one year.
The purpose of this project is the reintegration of the driver, since this will have to attend a course of rehabilitation on the road.
In addition to the General Prosecutor’s Office for Road Safety, the Directorate-General for Traffic (DGT) and the Fondazione Istituto Tecnologico per la Seguridad del Automotive (FITSA) will participate in this initiative.
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of motorists reported more than once for drunk driving then return to driving the car.
Alcohol would avoid this, because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not blow, or when a higher concentration of alcohol is detected than allowed.
The cost is more than 1000 euros and would be borne by the sanctioned.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with such devices allow to reduce up to 65% of the infringements committed during the first year of introduction.
And in Spain, it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people a year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to put a stop to these behaviors before they become criminal offences.
And to facilitate its development, since the legal reform can be carried out on an ordinary basis, and, no doubt, the necessary reform for the criminal procedure would require an organic law.
However, the device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial solution, although it has already been introduced experimentally in some industrial and public vehicles.
